White enamel with black ceramic stove top, 4 burners and warming area, a large capacity baking chamber, and pan storage drawer. - Laundry room with white enamel high efficiency washer and dryer. Laundry room accessible via bathroom and/or back porch.  - Window coverings provided (roller shades and gorgeous lace curtains in every room). - Front and back storm doors with sliding window and screen. This allows air to come through when desired.  - Tornado shelter. Shelter is accessible via trap floor in laundry room. The steps into the shelter are new and of solid construction. Credit and criminal checks required. Previous landlord references necessary.  Available now to a well qualified tenant. All utilities are tenant's responsibility. No smoking inside house or on property.  Features: - American Foursquare architecture (1895 to 1920).  This style incorporates elements of the Prairie School and the Craftsman styles. - Brand new Gerard stone-coated steel shingle roof. - High 10' ceilings and plaster walls. Fresh new paint. - Central air and heat. - Beautiful, original hardwood flooring in living room, master bedroom, and smaller bedroom.  - Bathroom is completely remodeled including: pedestal sink, antique-like etched mirror above sink, classic tile on walls from baseboard to waist high trimmed with metallic pewter tile, detachable hand-held shower head, curved shower curtain rod providing generous showering space, and updated faucets and hardware.  - Spacious, country style eat-in kitchen. - Classic retro style white metal kitchen cupboards and cabinets. - Brand new Kenmore white enamel refrigerator with freezer on the bottom. - Whirlpool electric stove. White enamel with black ceramic stove top, 4 burners and warming area, a large capacity baking chamber, and pan storage drawer. - Laundry room with white enamel high efficiency washer and dryer. Laundry room accessible via bathroom and/or back porch.  - Window coverings provided (roller shades and gorgeous lace curtains in every room). - Front and back storm doors with sliding window and screen. This allows air to come through when desired.  - Tornado shelter. Shelter is accessible via trap floor in laundry room. The steps into the shelter are new and of solid construction. There is electric lighting in the shelter. It is roomy, well-built, and provides a secure shelter in the event of a tornado.  - Electrical wiring from city pole to house is underground to protect from weather conditions such as: storms, ice, severe hail, high winds, falling tree branches, etc. minimizing the opportunity of a power outage due to downed power line to house.   Amenities: - Yard has: 2 large Black Locust trees which provide inviting shade, 2 Maple trees (Burgundy Belle and Red Sunset), 1 Prairie Fire Crab Apple tree, 2 Dwarf Korean Lilacs, 1 Wahoo bush, 2 Bridal Veil bushes, 1 White Peony, multiple Day Lilies, Rhubarb plant (great in pies or custards), White Hydrangea bush, Large Iris flower bed, and miscellaneous flowers such as Tulips, Daffodils, Golden Rod, etc. around the house.  - Large, detached garage built in 2007. Garage is: 26 ft. x 15 ft. (390 sq. ft.) with remote door opener. Multiple electrical outlets inside and outside the garage.  - Internet access available. - Family built, owned, and well maintained since 1919. - Great neighbors! - 1 block to Saint John Nepomucene Church & Elementary School (K - 6 & Pre-K classes), Weston NE. - 8 miles to Saunders Medical Center, Wahoo NE.  - 37 miles to University of Nebraska, Lincoln NE.  - 45 miles to Nebraska Medical Center, Omaha NE. - 55 miles to Eppley International Airport, Omaha NE. Fairbury 23 Apartments is a former high school that has been renovated into a low-income tax credit facility for seniors. The building is on the National Register of Historic Places and retains some of the original woodwork. Wide hallways make it ideal for residents who like to place decorations outside their units. Many units have teachers' closets, which add to the antique charm and provide additional storage. Spacious apartments with wide windows allow for plenty of sunlight. Many units have walk-in showers with corner seats, and grab bars are installed upon request. Most bathroom sinks have pedestal design. Kitchen appliances include garbage disposals, microwave ovens, dishwashers, and refrigerators with ice makers. Ovens have front-control panels. Lower cabinets have slide-out shelves. Residents control their own thermostats. Doors are handicapped accessible, the elevator is serviced quarterly, and state-inspected annually. The exterior doors are limited-access. Qualifying applicants have a monthly income of at least twice the cost of their monthly rent, and their income does not exceed a specific limit. Rent includes water, sewer, trash, basic cable, and off-street covered parking. Square footage varies from 814 to 1115.

As a Licensed Real Estate Agent, 4th Generation Colorado Native and Neighborhood Specialist, I know the market and have resources to help you with finding a rental home with purchase option. This Rent with Purchase Option Program provides responsible households a transparent new path to home ownership through its Lease with a Right to Purchase Program.  A qualifying applicant can choose just about any home for sale in an approved community.  Our investor buys the house, and then leases it to YOU, the consumer. There is NO purchase obligation, you can simply use the property as a rental if you wish.
